review_blob:
L: Clear gold. Excellent lacing, great white head with good retention.
S: Lager-ish. Malty.
T: Like it smells. Only fresher and a more drinkable version of a lager.
F: Light and smooth.
O: I like this style. Other good examples I have had is Alpine Spring from Sam Adams and Maxlrainers Zwickel Max. This is more readily available though.

Bought in Bad Aibling. Poured into Weiss glass.
Look: Copper with nice, thick and foamy head.
Smell: Typical Dunkelweizen. Nothing great or special.
Taste: Good and malty.
Feel: Very smooth.
Overall: Not bad. Probably not my favorite, but a decent example of the style.

Look: golden and clear. Good head.
Smell: Typical ESB, which is good.
Taste: Very nice. Balanced and sweet. Reminds me of the prime example of this style; Fullers ESB.
Feel: Smooth and slick.
Overall: Pretty spot-on, in my opinion. A great American attempt at the style. Would drink again.

I love a good Altbier. Definitely a pleasant surprise from KS. Picked up a six pack.
L: Clear amber with nice white head.
S: Malty and yeasty.
T: Balanced. Malt edge with nice aftertaste.
F: Medium and smooth.
O: Would have again. Great with food (pizza) or without.

Look: Nice. Good white foamy head.
Smell: Strong piney hops. Getting a sense Im going to be bowled-over.
Taste: Tastes like it smells. Strong hops up front, little substance otherwise.
Feel: Somewhat dry.
Overall: Ive tried many examples of this style, but the problem Im having is consistency. Hop content varies so much from beer to beer within the style that its hard to get a grip on what an American IPA is. Id probably put this with Dogfish Heads 90 Minute as a DIPA. Needs more character to be an AIPA, IMO.
Part of my balanced Bavarian meal. Very typical German pilsener; medium carbonation with healthy head, bright gold color, and balanced flavor. Nothing really stands out, just a solid pils.
From bottle bought in Bad Aibling. Very nice. Smooth, light, and refreshing. Very much like a Helles. Perfect with my pizza and a great hot weather style.

Very nice. Had this "vom fass" at the brewery. Fresh and delicious.
Lightly roasted malt scent, rich dark copper color, easy drinker with medium mouth feel. The best example of this style Ive had.
